    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted hemolysis index agrees with experimental measurements within combined simulation and measurement uncertainty at all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values show agreement at 4 of 5 operating points within combined uncertainty. At the highest flow-speed combination (6 L/min, 3500 RPM), the predicted NIH exceeds the experimental mean by 18%, which falls outside the combined uncertainty band of ±12%. Quantitative output comparison is therefore assessed at level 1, one step below the required level 2. The discrepancy is attributed to transitional flow effects near the volute tongue that the steady-state k-ω SST model does not fully resolve. This shortfall was noted in the internal review but the overall assessment team concluded the model remained fit for purpose given conservative direction of the error."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
